<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>How much does a Sprinter van wrap cost?</h3><p>A full Sprinter van wrap costs $3,750–$6,600 depending on wheelbase and roof height. Partial wraps start at $1,200. All pricing includes design, cast vinyl, UV overlaminate, and free pickup.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>Do you wrap high-roof Sprinters?</h3><p>Yes. High-roof and super high-roof Sprinters are our specialty. The additional surface area means more branding space and higher visibility on the road.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>How long does a Sprinter wrap take?</h3><p>Design: 2–5 business days. Installation: 2–3 days. Delivery back same day or next day.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>Can you wrap a Sprinter with a sliding door?</h3><p>Yes. Sliding door wraps are standard. The vinyl is precision-cut along the door track for clean operation.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>Will a wrap damage my Sprinter's paint?</h3><p>No. Cast vinyl wraps are fully removable without paint damage. Wraps actually protect the factory paint from UV, road salt, and minor scratches.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>Do you offer Sprinter fleet wraps?</h3><p>Yes. Fleet discounts: 3% for 2–4 vans, 7% for 5–9, 11% for 10–24, 15% for 25+. Same design across multiple Sprinters costs less per unit.</p></div>
<div class="faq-item"><h3>What about Ford Transit and RAM ProMaster?</h3><p>We wrap all cargo van brands with the same premium materials and process. We have exact templates for Transit, ProMaster, NV, Express, and Savana.</p></div>

